  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractAggregateOperator<T1,T2>
    An abstract implementation of AggregateOperator keeping a field for the current result.
    AbstractDAEFunction
    An abstract implementation of DAEFunction setting AbstractDAEFunction.isRandom() to false by default.
    AbstractRange<T>
    Provides basic Range functionality, only leaving to the user the task of defining NullaryFunction.apply(), which should provide a new iterator over a range of values.
    DefaultDependencyAwareEnvironment  
    DefaultRangeOperation<T1,T2>  
    RangeOperationsInterpreter
    RangeOperationsInterpreter is a facility for easily writing and efficiently computing expressions with nested aggregate operators (for example, \sum_i \prod_j f(i,j)).
